The President and Vice President met with the President's Homeland Security Council to discuss the urgent humanitarian situation at the border and the comprehensive response implemented by the Administration. The meeting noted a decline in daily apprehensions of unaccompanied children by Customs and Border Patrol. The Council committed to continuing efforts to deter illegal migration and provide care for those apprehended at the border. Participants discussed combating the root causes of migration and the need for additional resources. The Homeland Security Council was created in 2001 to coordinate homeland security issues.